properties.Name: Lakewood Community Center
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Lakewood Community Center is a multipurpose center, that includes a college-sized gymnasium, meeting rooms, and the Lakewood Senior Activity Center.

properties.Name: Sprinker Recreation Center
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Sprinker Recreation Center is part of Spanaway Regional Park, and includes many indoor and outdoor recreation facilities, including ice rink, raquet-sports and basketball courts, ballfields, and skatepark with many community activities.

properties.Name: Crescent Lake Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Public Works Surface Water Management

properties.Name: Frontier Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.ParkHours: Dawn to Dusk / During special events and the Pierce County Fair new times for gate closures at Frontier Park go into effect.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Frontier Park is a 71 acre complex on Meridian between Puyallup and Graham. The park is home to many uses, including the Pierce County Fair, Highland Games, equestrian shows, scouting events, car shows, quarter midget track racing, and other community events.

properties.Name: Spanaway Park
properties.Address: 14905 Bresemann Blvd S (and Military Road S)
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This 89-acre park is part of Spanaway Regional Park. The Park follows the east shoreline of Spanaway Lake and includes swimming beaches, boat launch, picnic shelters, playground, walking paths, and year-round activities.

properties.Name: Dawson Playfield
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Dawson Playfield is a neighborhood park in the Midland community that includes a picnic shelter, playground, basketball and tennis courts, playfield, and walking path.

properties.Name: Chambers Bay Golf Course
properties.DESCRIPTION: Located near Tacoma in Pierce County, Washington, Chambers Bay is one of the top public courses in the nation and the first course in the Northwest to welcome the U.S. Open Championship.

properties.Name: Lake Spanaway Golf Course
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Lake Spanaway Golf Course is part of the Spanaway Regional Recreational Complex that also contains Bresemann Forest, Sprinkler Recreation Center and Spanaway Park. The course includes 18 holes, a clubhouse, and driving range.

properties.Name: Gonyea Playfield
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This neighborhood playfield serves the Parkland community and includes multi-purpose baseball, softball and soccer fields with a playground, basketball courts, and restrooms.

properties.Name: Ashford County Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This 80-acre park in along SR-706 in the community of Ashford includes trails, playground, great lawn, restrooms, and an outdoor amphitheater.

properties.Name: Parkland Prairie Nature Preserve
properties.Address: Tule Lake Rd S At Yakima Ave S
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This 4.5 acre preserve of Garry Oak open space property is located in the Parkland area. This property includes a nature trail and educational kiosk.

properties.Name: Orangegate Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services

properties.Name: Seeley Lake Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Seeley Lake Park is a small park nestled between a busy street, retail stores, and an apartment complex. This 48-acre park includes a 1-mile soft-surface walking trail surrounding wetlands.

properties.Name: Herron Point
properties.Address: Isted Rd KN At N Herron Rd KN
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services

properties.Name: Riverside Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Located at Riverside Road and 78th Street Court in Sumner, Riverside Park is an undeveloped 36-acre park along the Puyallup River with four disc golf courses, seasonal BMX concession, and a permit-use only boat slide.

properties.Name: Lidford Playfield
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This neighbhorhood playfield serves the Summit-Waller community and includes a walking path and open lawn.

properties.Name: Bresemann Forest
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Bresemann Forest is part of Spanaway Regional Park and located adjacent to Sprinker Recreation Center. This urban forest includes nature trails.

properties.Name: Mayfair Playfield
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This neighborhood playfield serves the Parkland community and is located along Clover Creek. The park includes a playground and open lawn.

properties.Name: North Lake Tapps Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.ParkHours: 7:30 am - 8 pm from April through September
properties.DESCRIPTION: This popular swimming and boat launch area is located on the north side of Lake Tapps. The 135-acre site is mostly wooded and undeveloped with the exception of parking areas, boat launch, and swimming beach along the waterfront.

properties.Name: Nathan Chapman Trail
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Nathan Chapman Memorial Trail cuts through woods and wetlands, joining South Hill Community Park with Heritage Recreation Center, a public athletic complex. The trail is a wide, paved route that connects to a loop trail at South Hill Community Park.

properties.Name: Meridian Habitat Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: Known to locals as the Amphitheatre, Meridian Habitat Park is a 36-acre park that includes a community center, nature playground, dog park, amphitheater, walking paths, and a variety of wildlife habitat.

properties.Name: Purdy Sand Spit
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Purdy Sand Spit is an unimproved waterfront public area that runs right along SR 302. Its 7.5 acres includes a boat launch. A great place to see waterfowl such as sea gulls and blue heron.

properties.Name: Chambers Creek Regional Park
properties.DESCRIPTION: This is part of the Chambers Creek Regional Park complex, which includes 930-acres of park, golf course and canyon trails. The parks includes includes over two miles of saltwater shoreline and breathtaking mountain and Puget Sound views.

properties.Name: South Hill Community Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: The South Hill Community Park is a 40-acre site which includes, bathrooms, playground, picnic tables, multipurpose sports fields and a network of paved meandering trails, South Hill Loop Trail and Nathan Chapman Memorial Trail.

properties.Name: Swan Creek Park- Pioneer Way (Pierce County
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: This undeveloped park includes a gravel parking lot and soft surface nature trails along Swan Creek. Trails connect to Metro Parks Swan Creek Park nature trails.

properties.Name: Foothills Trail- South Prairie to Buckley
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.Maplabel: Foothills Trail- Buckley to South Prairie Section
properties.DESCRIPTION: This trail section extends from South Prairie Creek in the Town of South Prairie to Buckley. The main stem now stops at South Prairie, about three miles short of its planned end point on the edge of Buckley.

properties.Name: Foothills Trail- Meeker to McMillin
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.Maplabel: Foothills Trail- Meeker to McMillin Section
properties.DESCRIPTION: The East Puyallup to McMillin section of the Foothills Trail is four miles of trail that winds through trees and farms and runs alongside an active railway.

properties.Name: Foothills Trail- Orting to South Prairie
properties.Maplabel: Foothills Trail- Orting to South Prairie Section

properties.Name: Chambers Creek Canyon Park
properties.Manager: Pierce County Parks and Recreation Services
properties.DESCRIPTION: There are two soft-surface nature trails located within the Chambers Creek Canyon. One trail begins at Kobayashi Park and the other begins at Chambers Creek Road or Zircon Drive.

properties.DESCRIPTION: Snug in the curve of Carr Inlet a half-hour from Tacoma, Kopachuck State Park is an easy jaunt from South Puget Sound and the Kitsap Peninsula, and a lovely stop on an outing to Gig Harbor.
